==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Purist
<hw>Pur"ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>puriste</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One who aims at excessive purity or nicety, esp. in the
choice of language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He [Fox] . . . purified vocabulary with a scrupulosity unknown to
any <qex>purist</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who maintains that the New Testament was written
in pure Greek.</def> <rj><au>M. Stuart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Puristical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Puristic</ent>⟦br⟧
